Durban - Chatsworth Cluster commander, Major-General Madlenkosi Chirwa, has said that their detectives are working around the clock to locate the third man, wanted for a botched hijacking that claimed the life of Sadia Sukhraj. On Monday, Sukhraj was seated in her family's Hyundai iX35 when it was hijacked by three men. The driver lost control of the vehicle and crashed into a truck before veering down an embankment. One of the men died at the scene, while a second was nabbed. On Wednesday, Sbonelo Mkhize, appeared briefly in the Durban Magistrates Court. He faces charges of murder, kidnapping and theft.At her funeral on Tuesday, hundreds of mourners gathered  to celebrate the life of the 9-year-old.
Her parents, Pastor Shailendra and Lorraine Sukhraj, were in tears throughout the service, holding on to each other for support. 

At the cemetery, they kissed their daughter goodbye, her mother telling her she loved her and her father saying he did all he could. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

White doves were released as she was buried, and her father found the strength to sing and pray, thanking God for the time he had with his “princess”. 















